---
/**
 * Security Considerations, Versioning, and JSON Schema sections.
 */
---

<section id="security" class="mb-16">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">10. Security Considerations</h2>
  <div class="rounded-xl border border-yellow-500/30 bg-yellow-500/5 p-6 mb-6">
    <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-yellow-400 mb-2">Warning: API Field</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">
      The <code class="text-primary bg-surface-light px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">api</code> field
      contains JavaScript expressions that tools may execute in the page context. Consumers
      of this field <strong class="text-white">must not</strong> execute API expressions from
      untrusted or unverified sources.
    </p>
  </div>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted space-y-3">
    <li>
      <strong class="text-white">Origin validation:</strong> Only read the declaration file from
      the same origin it is served on. Never execute API expressions from a third-party-hosted
      declaration file.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-white">Content-Type checking:</strong> Verify the response has
      <code class="text-primary bg-surface-light px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">application/json</code>
      content type before parsing.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-white">Schema validation:</strong> Validate against the
      <a href="/standard/v1/schema.json" class="text-primary hover:underline">JSON Schema</a>
      before processing. Reject malformed files.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-white">API expression sandboxing:</strong> If executing
      <code class="text-primary bg-surface-light px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">api</code>
      expressions, run them in a sandboxed context. Never pass unsanitized strings to
      code evaluation functions without validation.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-white">File integrity:</strong> Consider implementing
      Subresource Integrity (SRI) or signature verification for high-security deployments.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-white">Rate limiting:</strong> Consumers should cache the declaration
      file and avoid fetching it on every page load. A TTL of 1 hour is recommended.
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section id="versioning" class="mb-16">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">11. Versioning</h2>
  <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
    The standard uses semantic versioning with two components:
    <code class="text-primary bg-surface-light px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">major.minor</code>.
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted space-y-2">
    <li>
      <strong class="text-white">Minor versions</strong> (1.0 &rarr; 1.1) are backward-compatible.
      New optional fields may be added. Existing fields retain their meaning.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-white">Major versions</strong> (1.x &rarr; 2.0) may introduce breaking
      changes: renamed fields, changed semantics, removed fields, or new required fields.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mt-4">
    Consumers should check the <code class="text-primary bg-surface-light px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">version</code>
    field and handle unknown major versions gracefully. If a consumer only understands v1.x,
    it should skip a v2.0 file rather than misinterpret it.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="json-schema" class="mb-16">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">12. JSON Schema</h2>
  <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
    The official JSON Schema for v1.0 is available for download and can be used to validate
    declaration files in editors, CI pipelines, and automated tools.
  </p>
  <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
    <a
      href="/standard/v1/schema.json"
      download
      class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 rounded-lg bg-primary hover:bg-primary-dark text-white font-medium transition-colors"
    >
      Download schema.json
    </a>
    <a
      href="https://github.com/zentala/cookies-accepter/tree/main/packages/schema"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 rounded-lg border border-white/20 hover:border-white/40 text-white font-medium transition-colors"
    >
      View on GitHub
    </a>
  </div>
  <div class="mt-6 rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-surface-light p-4">
    <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-2">Use in your editor (VS Code, JetBrains):</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <pre class="text-sm"><code class="text-muted">{`{
  "$schema": "https://nocookie.org/standard/v1/schema.json",
  "version": "1.0",
  "categories": ["essential"]
}`}</code></pre>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
